#!/usr/bin/env python3
"""
GCP Resource Label Remover

Fetches labeled resources across GCP services, removes their labels,
and produces an audit CSV report.

Services covered:
  compute         - Instances, Disks, Snapshots, Images
  networking      - Forwarding Rules (regional + global), VPN Gateways,
                    External VPN Gateways
  gcs             - Cloud Storage Buckets
  bigquery        - Datasets, Tables
  gke             - GKE Clusters
  pubsub          - Topics, Subscriptions
  run             - Cloud Run Services
  functions       - Cloud Functions (gen2)
  sql             - Cloud SQL Instances
  kms             - Cloud KMS Crypto Keys
  secretmanager   - Secret Manager Secrets
  monitoring      - Cloud Monitoring Alert Policies
  dns             - Cloud DNS Managed Zones
  artifactregistry- Artifact Registry Repositories
  vertexai        - Vertex AI Datasets, Models, Endpoints
  vertexaisearch  - Vertex AI Search / Discovery Engine Data Stores
  dataplex        - Dataplex Lakes, Zones, Assets
  notebooks       - Vertex AI Workbench Instances
  workstations    - Cloud Workstations Clusters, Configs, Workstations
  healthcare      - Cloud Healthcare Datasets, DICOM / FHIR / HL7v2 Stores
  scheduler       - Cloud Scheduler Jobs
  datacatalog     - Data Catalog Entry Groups

Notes on services without label support in the GCP API:
  - Cloud Logging   : LogBucket / LogSink have no labels field
  - App Engine      : Service / Version resources have no labels API
  - Cloud Tasks     : Queue (v2) has no labels field
  - VM Manager      : Patch deployments have no labels field
  - Velostrata/C2D  : Resources are standard Compute VMs/images (use 'compute')

Usage:
    python gcp_label_remover.py --project my-project --dry-run
    python gcp_label_remover.py --project my-project --execute
    python gcp_label_remover.py --project my-project --execute --services kms,secretmanager,bigquery
    python gcp_label_remover.py --project my-project --dry-run --label-keys costcentre,apmid
    python gcp_label_remover.py --project my-project --execute --label-keys costcentre,apmid
    python gcp_label_remover.py --project my-project --dry-run \
        --label-keys costcentre,apmid --fuzzy-threshold 0.82

Label key filtering (--label-keys):
    When --label-keys is provided, only labels whose KEY matches one of the
    supplied names are removed. All other labels on the resource are preserved.
    Resources that do not carry any of the target keys are skipped entirely.
    When omitted, ALL labels are removed (original behaviour).

Fuzzy / variant key matching (--fuzzy-threshold):
    Real-world label keys are often misspelled or formatted differently across
    projects and teams. Three matching layers are applied in order:

      1. Exact   (case-insensitive)  costcentre  == Costcentre
      2. Normalized (strip - _ space) cost-centre == cost_centre == costcentre
      3. Fuzzy   (edit-distance)     costcanter  ~~ costcentre   (if threshold set)

    --fuzzy-threshold sets the minimum similarity ratio (0.0–1.0) for layer 3.
    A value of 0.82 catches most single-character typos while avoiding false
    positives. Default is 0.0 (fuzzy matching disabled).

    Every fuzzy / normalised match is logged as a WARNING and recorded in the
    audit CSV under the key_matches column so you can review what was matched.
"""

